parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear leaf spring assembly can cause the vehicle body to drop to the ground, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle body drops to the ground
the rear of the vehicle suddenly rises or falls
loud noises from the rear of the vehicle
uneven vehicle ride or handling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ball Joint and CV Joint Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joint and CV joints can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle drops to the ground
loud noises from the front of the vehicle
uneven vehicle ride or handling
difficulty steering the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The rear of the vehicle suddenly rises or falls
loud noises from the rear of the vehicle
uneven vehicle ride or handling
difficulty controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving in rainy or snowy conditions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers turn off or on unexpectedly
wipers change speed on their own
wipers fail to turn off when switched off
wipers malfunction sporadically
wipers work intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power and stalling can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, as the vehicle may lose braking and steering capabilities, leaving the driver with limited time to react.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the vehicle accelerates poorly or not at all
the engine RPMs fluctuate erratically
the oil pressure gauge reads abnormally
the vehicle overheats
and the radiator may rust on the inside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine and other components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the vehicle shuts down
the radiator rusts on the inside
and the vehicle blows out cool air.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Radiator failure can cause engine overheating, leading to damage to the engine and other components, and potentially causing accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The radiator rusts on the inside
the engine overheats
and the vehicle shuts down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of steel brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of brake function, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
brake warning light illuminates
brake fluid leaking from the vicinity of the left rear wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty anti-lock brake sensor can cause the anti-lock brakes to malfunction, leading to unexpected and sudden braking, which can cause accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Anti-lock brakes kick in at low speeds (5-10 mph)
unexpected and sudden braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of one or both HID headlights can significantly reduce visibility at night, increasing the risk of accidents and compromising road safety.
symptoms: One or both HID headlights do not function
the vehicle operates with only one headlight at night
intermittent or complete failure of the HID lamp.
